{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/an-unexpected-cultural-and-history-lesson/","result":{"data":{"site":{"id":"Site","siteMetadata":{"title":"Where is Xinlu"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"273130c0-5499-5a87-b5f9-af5fac9dcac7","excerpt":"My original plan in New Mexico involves visting the 2 national parks and meeting some friends at Santa Fe. As I’ve quickly learned, plans in the time of coronavirus not only cannot be set in stone - they might as well be sands getting blown in the wind. So as the national parks closed and friend-meeting got cancelled…","html":"<p>My original plan in New Mexico involves visting the 2 national parks and meeting some friends at Santa Fe. As I’ve quickly learned, plans in the time of coronavirus not only cannot be set in stone - they might as well be sands getting blown in the wind. So as the national parks closed and friend-meeting got cancelled, I grabbed onto the closest thing open near Albuquerque: Petroglyph &#x26; Bandalier National Monuments.</p>\n<p>As luck has it, this unexpected turn of event set me down a 3 day journey to discover and learn about the history and incredible architecture of the ancestral Puebloans - a word I don’t recall ever seeing before, not to mention knowing anything about. </p>\n<p>With spotty-or-non-existent internet along the way, I had the joy of discovering new information the old-fashioned way without the help of Google (or from all the closed visitor centers/museums due to coronavirus). It was like solving a puzzle: after seeing many ruins in different places, I started to notice similarities/unusual features, and missing pieces in one ruin would make a lot of sense after seeing the next ruin. After I visited the final stop of this journey, Mesa Verde National Park with its excellent explanatory signage, the puzzle pieces were coming together in a most satisfactory way. Such is the joy of making the best out of the unexpected!</p>\n<p>Some highlights:</p>\n<p>I came to Bandalier National Monument with zero expectation (only because it is open), so imagine my delight when I saw this at the end of a pleasant but unremarkable hike:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/72e01/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"IMG 20200322 165501\"\n        title=\"IMG 20200322 165501\"\n        src=\"/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/1c72d/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/a80bd/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg 148w,\n/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/1c91a/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg 295w,\n/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/1c72d/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg 590w,\n/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/a8a14/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg 885w,\n/where-am-i/static/216ef8b3f950e262e27f7843c19851ec/72e01/IMG_20200322_165501.jpg 1024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n… or that I get to climb 3 tall ladders to reach a house perched in middle of a rock wall:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/where-am-i/static/4fc187baa604b4117cbef0f35b298ab8/212bf/IMG_20200322_173516.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"IMG 20200322 173516\"\n        title=\"IMG 20200322 173516\"\n        src=\"/where-am-i/static/4fc187baa604b4117cbef0f35b298ab8/1c72d/IMG_20200322_173516.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/where-am-i/static/4fc187baa604b4117cbef0f35b298ab8/a80bd/IMG_20200322_173516.jpg 148w,\n/where-am-i/static/4fc187baa604b4117cbef0f35b298ab8/1c91a/IMG_20200322_173516.jpg 295w,\n/where-am-i/static/4fc187baa604b4117cbef0f35b298ab8/1c72d/IMG_20200322_173516.jpg 590w,\n/where-am-i/static/4fc187baa604b4117cbef0f35b298ab8/212bf/IMG_20200322_173516.jpg 768w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In truly middle of nowhere (after driving on some scarily bumpy unpaved road), a grand sight in Chaco National Historical Park:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/72e01/DSC01182.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 48.63281250000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"DSC01182\"\n        title=\"DSC01182\"\n        src=\"/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/1c72d/DSC01182.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/a80bd/DSC01182.jpg 148w,\n/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/1c91a/DSC01182.jpg 295w,\n/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/1c72d/DSC01182.jpg 590w,\n/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/a8a14/DSC01182.jpg 885w,\n/where-am-i/static/bfe2950c065caf9a9b86482c70b16d83/72e01/DSC01182.jpg 1024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>And impressive setting for some impressive engineering in the form of cave dwellings (Cliff Palace, Mesa Verde):\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/72e01/DSC01208.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.86328125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"DSC01208\"\n        title=\"DSC01208\"\n        src=\"/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/1c72d/DSC01208.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/a80bd/DSC01208.jpg 148w,\n/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/1c91a/DSC01208.jpg 295w,\n/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/1c72d/DSC01208.jpg 590w,\n/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/a8a14/DSC01208.jpg 885w,\n/where-am-i/static/2f7ac82877b7bb80d7c012e3bdc1d80c/72e01/DSC01208.jpg 1024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This unexpected journey took me to southwestern Colorado. Now I’m already here, I decided that I might as well drive along the scenic <a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/articles/colorado-scenic-byway-san-juan-skyway\">San Juan Skyway</a> and soak in some mountain scenary, especially now that the Rocky Mountain National Park is closed.</p>\n<p>While visiting these national parks and monuments, I’ve only seen at most a handful of cars and other visitors - and oftentimes I was the only one around - in spaces that are clearly designed to handle significantly more crowd. In my (clearly biased) worldview right now, completely shutting down national parks seem like ~an extreme reaction~ [read the actual news article in addition to the headline now that I have internet: seems like Yellowstone etc. may have different visitor pattern than what I’ve seen in other parks. If that is true, perhaps shutdown makes sense] , instead of simply shuttering all lodging options to discourage crowd forming. Gloomy thoughts in my mind tonight as I found out that Yellowstone and Grand Teton are joining the ever growing list of closed places, but at least I have this starry night to comfort me:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/72e01/DSC01243.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.69921875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"DSC01243\"\n        title=\"DSC01243\"\n        src=\"/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/1c72d/DSC01243.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/a80bd/DSC01243.jpg 148w,\n/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/1c91a/DSC01243.jpg 295w,\n/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/1c72d/DSC01243.jpg 590w,\n/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/a8a14/DSC01243.jpg 885w,\n/where-am-i/static/11a3d6d878fb25cf3fa6de4be49214a2/72e01/DSC01243.jpg 1024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"An Unexpected Cultural and History Lesson","date":"March 25, 2020","description":""}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/an-unexpected-cultural-and-history-lesson/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/updates-courtesy-of-coronavirus/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Updates, courtesy of coronavirus"}},"next":null}}}